data.enText: almost correct or accurate, but not completely so
an approximate number/total/cost
data.chText: 约数；概算总额；约计成本

data.enText: The cost given is only approximate.
Use these figures as an approximate guide in your calculations.
data.chText: 在你的计算中把这些数字作为近似参考数值。

data.enText: to be similar or close to sth in nature, quality, amount, etc., but not exactly the same
The animals were reared in conditions which approximated the wild as closely as possible.
data.chText: 这些动物是在尽量近似自然的环境下饲养的。

data.enText: The total cost will approximate £15 billion.
His story approximates to the facts that we already know.
data.chText: 他的陈述和我们已掌握的事实接近。

data.enText: to calculate or estimate sth fairly accurately
a formula for approximating the weight of a horse
data.chText: 估算一匹马重量的公式

data.enText: The flight takes approximately three hours.
data.chText: 飞行时间大约需要三小时。

data.enText: The tickets cost about £20 each.
The repairs will cost $200, give or take a few dollars.
data.chText: 修理费要花200元，出入不过几元。

data.enText: How much will it cost, more or less ?
We are expecting thirty or so people to come.
data.chText: 我们预计要来三十人左右。

data.enText: She must be 25 or thereabouts .
Profits have fallen by roughly 15%.
You can expect to earn round about £40,000 a year.
data.chText: 你可望一年赚4万英镑左右。

data.enText: The price is somewhere around $800.
She earns somewhere in the region of £25,000.
All these words and phrases are used in both speaking and writing; about is the most common and approximately the most formal.
data.chText: 上述各词和短语在口语和书面语中均可使用，about最通用，approximately最正式。

simple_means.memory_skill: ap- 朝,向 + proxim 靠近,接近 + -ate 做,造成

tr: judge tentatively or form an estimate of (quantities or time)
example: I estimate this chicken to weigh three pounds
approximate leaves grow together but are not united

value.boxr_value: The adjective is pronounced /ə'prɒksɪmət/. The verb is pronounced /ə'prɒksɪmeɪt/. 形容词读作 /ə'prɒksɪmət/，动词读作 /ə'prɒksɪ- meɪt/。

example.ex: The approximate cost varies from around £150 to £250...
example.tran: 费用大概介于150至250英镑之间。

value.def: An approximate number, time, or position is close to the correct number, time, or position, but is not exact.

example.ex: Approximately $150 million is to be spent on improvements.
example.tran: 大约1.5亿美元将用于作出改善。

example.ex: They did not have even an approximate idea what the Germans really wanted.
example.tran: 他们完全不清楚德国人真正想要什么。

value.def: An idea or description that is approximate is not intended to be precise or accurate, but to give some indication of what something is like.

example.ex: Something approximating to a fair outcome will be ensured...
example.tran: 保证会有大致公正的结果。

example.ex: By about 6 weeks of age, most babies begin to show something approximating a day/night sleeping pattern.
example.tran: 到6个星期大时，大多数婴儿开始表现出近似于日夜分明的睡觉模式。

value.def: If something approximates to something else, it is similar to it but is not exactly the same.

trans: 近似公式；近似公式,近真公式；近似式
近似数，近似值；大概的数目
近似处理近似计算；近似计算
